Application Name: Task Tracker 2.765.32564

Application Discription: 
Our idea is a corporate task tracker where employees log in to 
create and manage work-order style tasks that can be assigned to contractors and moved through 
statuses and steps on a bulletin-board (Kanban) view. Each task includes a real-world location, a
nd the app uses the Google Maps API to let users search/drop a pin and to display tasks on a map for q
uick planning. It runs on a Node/Express middle layer with PostgreSQL storing users (hashed passwords) 
and task data, with session-based login/logout, all packaged in Docker containers for portability. 
Our tracker is tailored for hypothetical real world "worksites" storing and maintaining sets of data a
nd work history for each "worksite" as they evolve while only revealing the necessary portion of up-to-date 
information to assigned contractors at that site. This is all done with a secure and user friendly UI that 
lets any manager easily check in on or update operation tasks.

Audience:
Our application is designed for corporate work environments where multiple teams need a clear and efficient 
way to coordinate task-based operations. It is especially useful for managers and office staff in coordinating 
with field employees and contractors, who work together across various disciplines and locations. The app 
supports organizations that manage real-world worksites and need a centralized system to assign tasks, track progress,
maintain operations and work history, and share privileged information with the people who need it in real time. 
Using a Kanban-style task board with location tracking, allows for a user-friendly and secure application to help 
teams improve communication, planning, and accountability, with a focus on workflow efficiency.


